cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a problem of reconstructing a tile packing from its row and column projections, which involves combinatorial and geometric aspects. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The problem also involves counting and optimization, which are related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the NP-hardness of the problem, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
